article.headline: Jackson State 73, Lipscomb 64
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Julius Young scored 19 points to lead Jackson State to a 73-64 victory over Lipscomb on Saturday night. Jackson State (4-6) scored the first nine points of the first half and never trailed. Trey Johnson scored 15 points and Dakari Wallace had 11 for the Tigers, who shot 49 percent for the game. Lipscomb (4-4) beat Jackson State 75-62 a week ago and had a three-game winning streak. The Bisons rallied in the second half, shooting 50 percent from the floor to pull within 68-61 on a basket from Eddie Ard with 31 seconds left. But Young responded with a basket and foul shot with 26 seconds remaining to push the lead back to 71-61, giving Jackson State its second straight win. The Tigers controlled the action in the first half and led 34-21 at halftime. Brian Fisk led Lipscomb with 19 points. Shaun Durant had 13 points and Ard added 11.
